Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.58,0:52:19.48,English,,0,0,0,,And the third difference is pre -capitalistic.\N{\rChinese}第三点差异是前资本主义的差异。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.06,0:52:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,Today, we do things to make money.\N{\rChinese}今天我们把事情做成了…
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.14,0:52:24.76,English,,0,0,0,,We come to school because we want to get a job\N{\rChinese}我们来到学校是因为想要上班
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.26,0:52:27.18,English,,0,0,0,,because we want to make money and we want to buy things.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.54,0:52:30.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's a very utilitarian mindset.\N{\rChinese}好的？这是一种非常实用主义的思维。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.66,0:52:36.08,English,,0,0,0,,But, for most of human history, most civilizations were not capitalistic.\N{\rChinese}但…我想把……
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.14,0:52:39.28,English,,0,0,0,,They were religious They were focused on community.\N{\rChinese}他们是宗教的，他们专注于社区。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.94,0:52:44.12,English,,0,0,0,,They were focused on what they could contribute to the betterment of the people around them.\N{\rChinese}他们专注于他们能为周围人们的好事做贡献。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.44,0:52:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,They were concerned about their relationship with God.\N{\rChinese}他们关注与上帝的关系。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.82,0:52:51.84,English,,0,0,0,,They were concerned about how to create peace in the world.\N{\rChinese}他们关注如何在世界上创造和平。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.98,0:52:54.64,English,,0,0,0,,They were asking big questions like what is good and what is evil?\N{\rChinese}他们在问大问题：什么是好，什么是坏？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.74,0:52:57.28,English,,0,0,0,,What is justice? What is fairness?\N{\rChinese}???
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.42,0:53:01.98,English,,0,0,0,,What is justice? And so,\N{\rChinese}????
